{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17496558","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17496558"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T08:50:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T08:50:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1382"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1382"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.15,0.05,0.02,0.74]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1382"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84774"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1382"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1382"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69066"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1091"},{"type":"tags","id":"3320"},{"type":"tags","id":"3521"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"6315"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6615"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42299"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43980"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44866"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84774","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/84774"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with worsening headaches and nausea over several months. The headaches have progressed over the last four weeks to occurring at least once daily, particularly in the morning. She experiences associated nausea during these episodes. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 124/62 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. Visual field testing reveals bitemporal hemianopia. The remainder of the neurological examination is normal. MRI of the brain is performed (Image 1, 2).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rathke cleft cyst","Craniopharyngioma","Meningioma","Chordoma","Pituitary adenoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features of raised intracranial pressure (morning headaches with nausea) and bitemporal hemianopia, suggesting compression of the optic chiasm. The MRI shows a sellar mass with suprasellar extension.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPituitary adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis as it is the most common sellar mass in adults, accounting for approximately 15% of all intracranial neoplasms. These tumours may be functionally active or non-functioning, with about 40% having no evidence of endocrine dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERathke cleft cysts\u003C/strong\u003E are benign, epithelium-lined cysts believed to originate from remnants of Rathke\u0027s pouch. They typically appear as well-circumscribed cystic lesions on MRI and rarely grow large enough to cause significant mass effect on the optic chiasm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECraniopharyngiomas\u003C/strong\u003E are rare epithelial tumours that arise from remnants of the craniopharyngeal duct. While they can occur in adults, they are more commonly seen in children and typically show calcification and both solid and cystic components on imaging.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeningiomas\u003C/strong\u003E arising in the sellar region are typically extra-axial masses that demonstrate a characteristic dural tail sign on contrast-enhanced MRI, which is not seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChordomas\u003C/strong\u003E are rare, slow-growing malignant tumours that typically arise from the clivus. They characteristically show bone destruction and tend to grow in a midline location with anterior-posterior extension, features not seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The commonest cause of a sellar mass in the adult population is a pituitary adenoma","Bitemporal hemianopia suggests compression of the optic chiasm by a sellar mass","Morning headaches with nausea suggest raised intracranial pressure from a space-occupying lesion"],"references":["Gaillard F. Meningioma. In: Radiology Reference Article - Radiopaedia.org [online]. 2022 [cited 23 July 2022]. Available at: https://radiopaedia.org/articles/meningioma?lang=gb","Alleyne C, Woodall M, Citow J. Neurosurgery board review. 3rd ed. Thieme; 2016.","Banskota S, Adamson DC. Pituitary Adenomas: From Diagnosis to Therapeutics. Biomedicines. 2021 Apr 30;9(5):494. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8146984/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69066"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1382"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19955"},{"type":"media","id":"19956"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19955"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/1170c5f6-14d9-4e83-872f-7cc3e5d8da4e.jpg","thumbU